

Six people were killed and one was injured in a traffic accident happening on Friday afternoon in the county of Songming, Southwest China's Yunnan Province.

The local police source said the tragedy occurred at about 2:40 p.m. in the county's Adalong village when a heavy-duty truck loaded with coal collided with a mini bus.

Six people on the bus, including a two-year-old boy, were killed on the spot and the injured has already been hospitalized, said the police.

Investigation into the cause of the accident is already underway.

